         <abstract>
            <p>
               We present all solutions to the equation ∑&lt;sub&gt;p∣ N&lt;/sub&gt;1/p + 1/N = 1 with at most eight primes, improve the bound on the nonsolvability of the Erdös-Moser equation ∑&lt;sup&gt;m-1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;j=1&lt;/sub&gt; j&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt; = m&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt;, and discuss the computational search techniques used to generate examples of perfectly weighted graphs. 
            </p>
          </abstract>
